Canadian Employment Insurance Recipients Dropped 3% in March

-- B y   I l a n   K o l e t   a n d   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 
2011-05-19T12:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-19/canadian-employment-insurance-recipients-dropped-3-in-march.html
The number of Canadians receiving
jobless benefits fell for the sixth straight month in March,
 Statistics Canada  said.  The number of regular beneficiaries declined 3 percent to
606,240 on a seasonally adjusted basis, with declines reported
in every province, led by Ontario.  From the year-ago month, the total number of claimants fell
9.9 percent, the Ottawa-based agency said today.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Ilan Kolet in Ottawa at   ikolet@bloomberg.net ;
